author: Logan Newman , The Republic | azcentral.com
title: Peoria man with traumatic brain injury reported missing
text:
Peoria Police Department is searching for Stephen Nunn, 20. He has a traumatic brain injury and went missing in the middle of the night. (Photo: Peoria Police Department) 
316 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN 1 COMMENT EMAIL MORE The Peoria Police Department says it is looking for a man with a traumatic brain injury who went missing in the middle of the night.
Stephen Nunn, 20, was last seen at his home near 67th Avenue and Bloomfield Road around 12:30 a.m. Thursday.
Police say Nunn is unable to take care of himself and is "under constant supervision." The report added that Nunn has "severe anxiety" and might hide. He would also appear to be disoriented, police said.
Nunn is described as a white man, 5 feet 8 inches tall, 170 pounds, with short brown hair and blue eyes, and he was last seen wearing gray pajama bottoms and a blue T-shirt.
Police ask anyone who sees him to contact the department's non-emergency number at 623-773-8311.
